article.headline: Cal Poly 91, Stanislaus State 72
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Dreshawn Vance had a game-high 17 points in his home debut Monday as Cal Poly beat Division II Cal State Stanislaus 91-72. The junior forward came off the bench to hit six of his seven floor shots as Cal Poly lead through the whole game. Senior forward Derek Stockalper added 16 points and seven rebounds. Cal Poly hit 52.4 percent as a team. The Warriors (1-3) shot 36.5 percent from the field and hit just five of 26 from 3-point range.
